), dorsally suffused with shining black scales; apical portion with a fuscous patch extending toward the termen and apex with a bronze as with orange-ocherous color encroaching on the apex and a small white spot at tornus; cilia light gray, with a white spot at beginning of costal cilia, remainder of cilia with black scales at base. Hindwing light gray, slightly infuscated towards apex, cilia light gray. Abdomen light gray, white beneath. Legs mostly light gray, white beneath.
